      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_ManualBilling_MarkRecordsAsProcessed",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to update records in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ManualBill.AccountManualBillingHeader",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table. It marks records as processed for a specified billing period and utility company by setting the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ProcessedInTheCurrentPeriod",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " field to 'Y'. This prevents these records from being processed again in future operations. The procedure also updates the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "LastUpdate",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " field with the current date and time. The procedure returns a status code indicating success or failure."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving a single "
